@Andrzej

Baseball is the outlier among American sports, as it is the only one of the major sports that is not a back-and-forth sport, where the point of the game is throw the ball (basketball),kick the ball (soccer) or shoot the puck (ice hockey) into a goal, or get the ball over a goal line (American football). It's the only one of them in which the defense holds the ball.

All the others have game clocks that count down to zero, not up.  They use "nothing" or "O" to refer to zero in scores (and ball-and-strike counts in baseball).  A contest is called a game; match is for tennis, soccer and polo.  In all sports, players wear uniforms, although the top half may be called a jersey.  No kits in American sports.
